{
  "uuid": "62dc7c0e7e3b0b0051b0dc58d7919fd7",
  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Recruitment Specialist",
  "description": "<h3><strong>Key Responsibilities</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Assist in sourcing candidates through job portals, social media, and referrals</p></li><li><p>Screen resumes and conduct initial phone or video interviews</p></li><li><p>Coordinate interview schedules and follow-ups with candidates and hiring managers</p></li><li><p>Maintain accurate candidate records and recruitment reports</p></li><li><p>Support onboarding and induction processes for new hires</p></li><li><p>Collaborate with HR and department teams to meet hiring needs</p></li><li><p>Participate in ad-hoc recruitment projects and initiatives</p></li></ul><h3><strong>Requirements</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Minimum 18 years old</p></li><li><p>Good command of English, both written and spoken</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Organised, detail-oriented, and able to manage multiple tasks</p></li><li><p>Comfortable using email, spreadsheets, and basic HR software</p></li><li><p>Prior HR or recruitment experience is a plus but not required</p></li></ul><h3><strong>What We Offer</strong></h3><ul><li><p>Monthly salary <strong>SGD 2,400 – 3,000</strong></p></li><li><p>On-the-job training and mentorship</p></li><li><p>Exposure to recruitment processes and HR operations</p></li><li><p>Supportive team environment</p></li><li><p>Opportunities for career progression within HR and talent acquisition</p></li></ul><h3><strong>How to Apply</strong></h3><p>Shortlisted candidates will be contacted for a brief phone discussion, followed by a detailed walkthrough of the role and expectations.</p>",
